					<h3>Exploradorable</h3>
                    <p><a href="http://exploradorable.pbworks.com/w/page/29306804/FrontPage" target="_blank">Game Wiki</a></p>
                    <p>Exploradorable is an exploration game in which The player is a curious baby robot (Roy) exploring the "Baby Robot Artificial Intelligence Navigatory System" (BRAINS). The training program takes place inside a massive cube, each face of which has its own respective gravity; the cube part of it is simply awesome justification for making this game take place in one "room". The baby robot's goal is to solve the puzzles in the labyrinth and pass the Baby Robot Training Program to be a big-boy robot in the Big Boy Robot World.</p>
                    <p>The player must collect variously colored orbs from each color-zone. Each of these orbs will be used to power the portal in order to travel to a completely different location. The gameplay is not linear, and a player must revisit rooms multiple times in order to progress overall. The colors are merely themes, not visually restrictive mandates. Each level represents a color in the spectrum (ROYGBIV) and is based around a certain colored theme (ex. green level is a valley, red level is inside a volcano).</p>
                    <h3>Responsibilites</h3>
                    <p><a href="http://exploradorable.pbworks.com/w/page/29307301/Nicholas-Moore" target="_blank">My Wiki Page</a></p>
                    <p>The tasks appointed to me for the game development are as follows:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Draw orthographic images of the game protagonist, Roy the Robot;</li>
                            <li>Work on character and environmental modeling;</li>
                            <li>Lead the texturing team and texture various models;</li>
                            <li>Try and incorporate scorpions into the game as frequently as possible</li>
                        </ul>
